service.name: Supporting Jobless Families
service.description: The Supporting Jobless Families Programme (SJF) aims to support the long-term participation and productivity of parents who are out of work. The programme will support eligible customers in achieving: Better health and early development outcomes for their children by promoting the services and support available locally; Enhanced school readiness and school transitions for pre-school aged children by promoting the benefits of early childhood learning and education such as preschool; Looking for work by informing and supporting parents to increase their capacity to overcome prevocational barriers to employment and be more engaged in the community.
